/*
Problem: Greatest Common Divisor (GCD)

Given two positive integers n1 and n2, return their Greatest Common Divisor (GCD).

Approach (Euclid's Algorithm):
1. Repeatedly replace the larger number with the remainder obtained after dividing it by the smaller number.
2. Continue this process until one of the numbers becomes 0.
3. The other number is the GCD.
*/

class Solution {
public:
    int GCD(int n1, int n2) {
        while (n2 != 0) {
            int rem = n1 % n2;
            n1 = n2;
            n2 = rem;
        }

        return n1;
    }
};

/*
Time Complexity: O(log(min(n1, n2)))
Space Complexity: O(1)

Mistakes I Made:
1. Initially used the brute-force approach by checking every number from 1 to min(n1, n2).
2. Optimized the brute-force loop from n1 to min(n1, n2).
3. Learned Euclid's Algorithm, which repeatedly replaces:
      (n1, n2) → (n2, n1 % n2)
   until n2 becomes 0.
4. The remaining non-zero number is the GCD.
*/
